Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy for Youtube thumbnail grabber

Youtube thumbnail grabber (accessible at https://youtube-thumbnail-grabber.com/) places great importance on protecting the privacy of our users. This Privacy Policy outlines the various types of information gathered by Youtube thumbnail grabber and explains the purposes for which we utilize such information.

Should you have any further inquiries or need additional details regarding our Privacy Policy, please feel free to reach out to us.

The scope of this Privacy Policy is limited to our digital operations and pertains to visitors of our website concerning any information they share or that is collected through Youtube thumbnail grabber. This policy does not extend to information obtained through offline means or other channels outside of this website.

Consent
Your use of our website constitutes your acceptance of this Privacy Policy and indicates your agreement to abide by its provisions.

Information we collect
We will clearly explain what personal information is requested from you and the purpose for requesting such information at the time we ask you to provide it.

In the event that you reach out to us directly, we might obtain supplementary details about you, including but not limited to your name, email address, phone number, message content and/or any attachments you send, along with any other information you voluntarily share with us.

During the account registration process, we may request contact details from you, which could include your name, company name, physical address, email address, and phone number.

How we use your information
We utilize the information collected to detect and prevent fraudulent activities.

Google DoubleClick DART Cookie
Google serves as a third-party vendor on our platform. Google employs cookies, specifically DART cookies, to deliver advertisements to visitors of our site based on their browsing activity on www.website.com and other websites across the internet. Users have the option to opt out of DART cookies by accessing the Google advertising and content network Privacy Policy at: https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads

Advertising Partners Privacy Policies
This section provides a reference list where you can locate the Privacy Policy for each advertising partner associated with Youtube thumbnail grabber.

Third-party advertising servers and networks employ various technologies including cookies, JavaScript, and Web Beacons within the advertisements and links displayed on Youtube thumbnail grabber. These technologies transmit information directly to users' browsers. When this happens, your IP address is automatically captured by these third parties. The purpose of these technologies is to evaluate the performance of advertising campaigns and/or customize the advertising content displayed on websites you visit.

Please be aware that Youtube thumbnail grabber does not have the ability to access or manage cookies utilized by third-party advertising providers.

Third Party Privacy Policies
The Privacy Policy of Youtube thumbnail grabber does not govern the practices of other advertisers or external websites. Therefore, we recommend that you review the individual Privacy Policies of these third-party advertising servers to obtain comprehensive information. These policies may contain details about their data handling practices and provide guidance on opting out of specific features.

You have the ability to disable cookies through your browser's settings. For comprehensive guidance on managing cookies in specific web browsers, please refer to the official websites of those browsers.

CCPA Privacy Rights (Do Not Sell My Personal Information)
Pursuant to the CCPA, California residents are granted several rights, including the following:

The right to request that a business disclose the categories and specific details of personal data it has collected about consumers.

The right to request that a business delete personal data it has collected about a consumer.

The right to request that a business that sells personal data refrain from selling the consumer's personal data.

We commit to responding to any such requests within one month. To exercise any of these rights, please get in touch with us.

GDPR Data Protection Rights
We aim to ensure that you are completely informed about all your data protection entitlements. All users have the following rights:

Access rights – You are entitled to request copies of your personal data. A nominal fee may apply for this service.

Rectification rights – You are entitled to request corrections to any information you believe to be incorrect. Additionally, you may request that we supplement any information you believe to be incomplete.

Erasure rights – Under specific circumstances, you are entitled to request the deletion of your personal data.

Restriction of processing rights – Under specific circumstances, you are entitled to request limitations on the processing of your personal data.

Objection to processing rights – Under specific circumstances, you are entitled to object to our processing of your personal data.

Data portability rights – Under specific circumstances, you are entitled to request that we transfer the data we have collected to another organization or directly to you.

We commit to responding to any such requests within one month. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us.

Children's Information
Protecting children's safety online is a key focus of our efforts. We urge parents and guardians to actively supervise, engage with, and guide their children's internet usage.

Youtube thumbnail grabber does not intentionally collect any Personally Identifiable Information from individuals under 13 years of age. If you suspect that your child has submitted such information through our website, we strongly urge you to contact us without delay, and we will take immediate action to remove such information from our systems.

